  "name": "Nagaraja COU1 — Non-cannulated pedicle screw compression-bending credibility assessment",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for FEA prediction of ASTM F1717 static compression-bending performance of a non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw construct. COU1 is the validation activity itself — the FEA model ensemble (FDA, Ansys, DePuy Synthes) is compared against N=11 experimental constructs across two laboratories. All 13 V&V 40 factors assessed; one factor (Test conditions) is marked not-applicable at a borderline call with extensive rationale because the single ASTM F1717 standardised loading condition is the only physiologically and regulatorily recognised configuration for this device class, making gradation-based assessment inapplicable. Model risk level 3; assurance level Medium; decision Accepted.",
